ZH: 中国曾经经历过一段专制统治的历史。
EN: China has experienced a period of authoritarian rule in the past.

ZH: 这个国家的政权越来越偏向专制了。
EN: The government of this country is becoming more and more authoritarian.

ZH: 他们的统治方式趋向于专制主义。
EN: Their style of ruling tends towards authoritarianism.

ZH: 这个专制政府对言论自由进行了严格限制。
EN: The authoritarian government tightly restricts freedom of speech.

ZH: 他是这个专制制度的忠实拥护者。
EN: He is a loyal supporter of this authoritarian regime.

ZH: 在这个专制国家，人民没有参与政治的权利。
EN: In this authoritarian country, people don't have the right to participate in politics.

ZH: 当权者使用专制手段维持自己的统治。
EN: The ruling authorities use authoritarian means to maintain their power.

ZH: 这个国家需要从专制走向民主化。
EN: This country needs to move from authoritarianism towards democracy.

ZH: 专制制度对公民的权益造成了压迫。
EN: The authoritarian system oppresses the rights of citizens.

ZH: 动荡的时期常常出现专制统治。
EN: Authoritarian rule often arises during turbulent times.

ZH: 共谋专制的人得到了国家权力的掌控。
EN: Those conspiring for authoritarianism have gained control of the government.

ZH: 专制政权无视人民的需求。
EN: The authoritarian regime disregards the needs of the people.

ZH: 民主对抗专制，是一场长期的斗争。
EN: The struggle between democracy and authoritarianism is a long-lasting battle.

ZH: 专制的政体往往缺乏透明度。
EN: Authoritarian political systems often lack transparency.

ZH: 专制领导者压制异议，不容许批评。
EN: Authoritarian leaders suppress dissent and do not tolerate criticism.

ZH: 在这个专制社会，人们无法自由地表达自己的观点。
EN: In this authoritarian society, people cannot freely express their opinions.

ZH: 他因为反对专制政权而被关入监狱。
EN: He was imprisoned for opposing the authoritarian regime.

ZH: 当代世界正在逐渐远离专制体制。
EN: The contemporary world is gradually moving away from authoritarian systems.

ZH: 这个社会渴望摆脱旧有的专制结构。
EN: This society yearns to break free from the old authoritarian structure.
